  "explanation": "In determining the appropriate sentence, several factors were considered. Embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty and trust, especially for a professional accountant. However, there are significant mitigating factors present: the defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made good faith efforts to partially repay the stolen $25,000. The courtroom outburst demanding a 10-year sentence is entirely irrelevant to the legal standards guiding this decision. A lengthy prison term is counterproductive and unwarranted for a non-violent, first-time offender who is actively paying restitution. Therefore, a short period of incarceration is appropriate to serve as a punitive measure, which will be followed by a probationary period requiring full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
